title: 5 BASIC STRENGTH-SPORTS EXERCISES FOR KIDS
description:
Here's a perfect routine for kids to strengthen their muscles with just 5 basic and super-easy exercises!

The body develops and gets stronger as we get older, and it's very important that kids start exercising as early as possible. This way, when kids perform regular strengthening exercises, they'll not only have more energy throughout the day, but they'll also grow into adults with stronger bodies, which means they'll have less risk of health issues. These 5 compound exercises will help them perform better in any physical activity and they're so quick that your little ones can do them as many times as they want and can handle. This will certainly help them get stronger and healthier!

Let's get the kids and start this new workout! 💪

TIMECODES:

00:00 Squat
00:58 Rest
01:16 Lunges
02:02 Rest
02:28 Tricep Dips
03:07 Rest
03:25 Knee Push Ups
04:07 Rest

title: Roger Federer's Kryptonite (against Rafael Nadal)
description:
Rafael Nadal used a play called "The Battering Ram" to break down Roger Federer's backhand over the course of their storied rivalry.  The play was pretty simple, Rafa would just hammer crosscourt forehands at Federer's backhand until Federer would try to hit down the line to Nadal's backhand...

Most of the time, the quality of Federer's backhand wasn't enough to "escape" from the play, and Nadal would stay in control of the point.

title: Will Las Vegas’ Big Bet On Sports Like The Super Bowl Pay Off?
description:
Las Vegas’ evolution is ever apparent as it gears up for Super Bowl 58. What was once considered a sports pariah is now hosting the biggest U.S. sporting event of the year, and the event comes less than three months after the city held a Grand Prix Formula One race. That’s not all — Las Vegas now boasts two new entertainment facilities, the Sphere and Allegiant Stadium, adding new offerings like A-list performers.

The total number of visitors climbed to 40.8 million in 2023. Beyond all the fun and gambling, the region has also become popular with relocating businesses and homebuyers. However, there are some significant risks with being a desert city that could hinder Las Vegas’ growth as the planet warms. CNBC traveled to Vegas and met with locals and experts to learn more about Sin City’s explosive growth.

title: How To Deadlift With Perfect Technique (Step By Step)
description:
How to deadlift with perfect technique. Here are my 5 steps:

First: set your stance. Start with your shins about one inch from the barbell and your feet at hip width. For a sumo deadlift, you’ll take a wider stance but I’ll cover that separately. The bar should cross the middle of your foot. Point your toes slightly out.

Second: grab the bar. Set your hips back with nearly straight knees. Don’t make the common mistake of squatting down. A deadlift isn’t a squat. Grip the bar with your hands just outside your shins. An over/under grip, hook grip or strapped grip will keep the bar from slipping. Let your shins make contact with the bar – they should be pointed straight up.

Third: pull the slack out. Instead of ripping the bar, pull tension into the bar gradually.

Fourth: pull. Lift your chest up while thrusting your hips forward. Keep the bar in contact with your legs.

Fifth: lockout. Stand up straight and lift your chest up. Don’t shrug or squeeze your back at the top.

Lower the weight by setting your hips back and letting your knees bend. Keep the bar in tight so it lands back over the middle of your foot.

Computer vision technology is breathing new life into the sports broadcast experience - allowing teams and production teams alike to turn the sports experience into a digital twin that can be reskinned and transported to any environment, whether it's a virtual reality experience in fortnite or an augmented reality table top viewer for the game. title: Kiteboarding Is Awesome #kiteboarding #kiteboarder #awesome #sports #sport #kiteboardingzone
description:
Kiteboarding Is Awesome #kiteboarding #kiteboarder #awesome #sports #sport #kiteboardingzone 

Kiteboarding, a water sport that combines the elements of surfing, windsurfing, wakeboarding, and paragliding, stands out as an exhilarating adventure that captivates the hearts of thrill-seekers worldwide. Imagine harnessing the power of the wind, as you glide across the water's surface, performing jumps and tricks that defy gravity. This visceral experience, a blend of adrenaline and serenity, showcases why kiteboarding isn't just a sport; it's a transformative journey.

The appeal of kiteboarding lies in its unique ability to engage both the body and the mind. As you prepare to launch your kite and step onto your board, there's a moment of pure anticipation. The wind catches your kite, and suddenly, you're lifted into a world where you're in complete control yet wholly at the mercy of nature's elements. It's this dance with the wind and water that makes every session unpredictable and utterly captivating.

Kiteboarding does more than just provide an adrenaline rush; it's a gateway to a tight-knit community of passionate individuals. From beginners to seasoned professionals, kiteboarders share a bond forged by mutual respect for the sport and the environment. The beach becomes more than just a playground; it's a place where lifelong friendships are formed, stories are shared, and experiences are magnified.

Moreover, kiteboarding is an incredible way to connect with nature. There's something profoundly spiritual about being out on the water, feeling the sun on your skin, and the wind in your hair. It's a moment of escape from the hustle and bustle of daily life, a chance to reflect and find peace amidst the waves. This sport encourages an appreciation for the natural world, fostering a sense of responsibility to protect our oceans and beaches for future generations to enjoy.

The physical benefits of kiteboarding are equally impressive. It's a full-body workout that enhances strength, balance, and flexibility. Each session challenges you to push your limits, leading to improved fitness levels and a sense of achievement. The sport also has a steep learning curve, which means there's always something new to master. This continuous progression keeps the mind engaged and the body active, promoting a healthy lifestyle.

Kiteboarding isn't just a hobby; it's a lifestyle choice that embodies freedom, adventure, and a deep connection with the natural world. It offers an escape from the ordinary, a way to challenge oneself, and the opportunity to become part of a community that celebrates life to the fullest. Whether you're cruising over calm waters or soaring high above the waves, kiteboarding reminds us of the joy of living in the moment and the beauty of pursuing our passions.

In conclusion, kiteboarding is more than just a sport; it's an awesome adventure that offers a unique combination of thrills, personal growth, and connection. It appeals to our deepest desires for freedom, adventure, and belonging. Whether you're drawn to the physical challenge, the bond with nature, or the community spirit, kiteboarding has something to offer everyone. It's a reminder that in a world full of possibilities, choosing to ride the wind and waves is a powerful way to discover the essence of what it means to be truly alive.

title: The ONLY 7 Flexibility Exercises You Need! ✅
description:
The Big 7 of Flexibility ✅

I’ve heard the concept of the “Big 5” flexibility exercises from @BodyweightWarrior ; they are: the pike, the pancake, the middle split, the front split, and the bridge. I added 2 more to the list, which I’ll explain below.

The idea is that working on these exercises will give you enough flexibility for all other flexibility goals you may have. For example, working towards the bridge will take care of the hip flexors, lats, and chest, instead of having to think about these body parts separately as individual goals.

You will still work on these body parts separately. However, the intent of improving your bridge and focusing on a single position makes training “easier” and more straightforward than thinking of each joint and muscle in isolation.

1️⃣ The Resting Squat: This should be your entry point to flexibility work. It should become so comfortable that you could even eat in this position.

2️⃣ The Pike: Hamstring flexibility will serve you for a myriad of skills and even daily life activities.

3️⃣ The Pancake: Not necessary for real-life activities, but it will improve all compression skills like handstand presses, L-Sit, and V-Sit.

4️⃣ The Front Split: This one will take care of all the hip flexors and hamstring flexibility you might ever need.

5️⃣ The Middle Split: Arguably the hardest of the lower body exercises. Again, not directly applicable to real life, but extremely helpful for anything hand-balance related. It will ensure you have enough hip flexibility to spare.

6️⃣ The Bridge: This exercise will open your entire anterior chain (front of the body). Working on it will open the spine, shoulders, lats, chest, abs, and hip flexors to a great degree.

7️⃣ The German Hang: I added this exercise to the list to work the shoulders into extension, which none of the above exercises does.

📱 You can find Follow Along classes for each of these movements on my app!

I recommend focusing on 2 at a time, maximum 3, for the best results. Any other questions, ask below!

With Love,
Gabo

title: The ONLY 7 Flexibility Exercises You Need! ✅
description:
The Big 7 of Flexibility ✅

I’ve heard the concept of the “Big 5” flexibility exercises from @BodyweightWarrior ; they are: the pike, the pancake, the middle split, the front split, and the bridge. I added 2 more to the list, which I’ll explain below.

The idea is that working on these exercises will give you enough flexibility for all other flexibility goals you may have. For example, working towards the bridge will take care of the hip flexors, lats, and chest, instead of having to think about these body parts separately as individual goals.

You will still work on these body parts separately. However, the intent of improving your bridge and focusing on a single position makes training “easier” and more straightforward than thinking of each joint and muscle in isolation.

1️⃣ The Resting Squat: This should be your entry point to flexibility work. It should become so comfortable that you could even eat in this position.

2️⃣ The Pike: Hamstring flexibility will serve you for a myriad of skills and even daily life activities.

3️⃣ The Pancake: Not necessary for real-life activities, but it will improve all compression skills like handstand presses, L-Sit, and V-Sit.

4️⃣ The Front Split: This one will take care of all the hip flexors and hamstring flexibility you might ever need.

5️⃣ The Middle Split: Arguably the hardest of the lower body exercises. Again, not directly applicable to real life, but extremely helpful for anything hand-balance related. It will ensure you have enough hip flexibility to spare.

6️⃣ The Bridge: This exercise will open your entire anterior chain (front of the body). Working on it will open the spine, shoulders, lats, chest, abs, and hip flexors to a great degree.

7️⃣ The German Hang: I added this exercise to the list to work the shoulders into extension, which none of the above exercises does.

📱 You can find Follow Along classes for each of these movements on my app!

I recommend focusing on 2 at a time, maximum 3, for the best results. Any other questions, ask below!

With Love,
Gabo

Сначала объясню «секрет гибкости»:

Cкольжение фасции, о котором я говорю происходит как между разными группами мышц, так и между мышечными слоями.

👉 И при наклоне вперед происходит не только растяжка задней части бедра, но в большей степени скольжение двуглавой мышцы бедра по отношению к полусухожильной мышце, которые я показываю в видео в поперечном срезе бедра.

И для того, чтобы это скольжение происходило ЛЕГКО - необходимо чтобы ФАСЦИЯ, о которой я говорю - была ЖИДКОСТНО НАПИТАНА в достаточном количестве. 

И если произошло «залипание» слоев, то ваше отведение будет ограниченным. И мы начинаем думать что проблема в растяжке и укорочении, а в первую очередь проблема может быть в отсутствии здорового скольжения этих слоев.

Если вы на какой-то период времени ограничили движение (много сидите), вы тренируетесь в одной плоскости без использования амплитуды движения суставов, как это задумано от природы -  сначала это приводит к «усыханию» фасции. 

И если мы продолжаем не двигаться и «ограничено тренироваться», постепенно начинают образовываться дополнительные коллагеновые волокна. Образуется рубцовая ткань, и она образуя спайку уже ограничивает движение на столько, что не представляется возможным его как-то вернуть. И это самая страшная ситуация.

👉 Что будем делать?

Работать с качеством движения фасции через правильное-разнообразное движение, а не классическую растяжку и тренировки. 

На своем YouTube канале я преподаю уроки, которые улучшают гибкость и «напитывают» фасцию, на ряду с выносливостью и силой. (Канал - «Пенкин Егор: Здоровое Будущее»)

P.S. ⚡️Новый старт программы «Здоровое Будущее», где мы формируем разнообразный двигательный опыт, как это заложено от природы - мы начинаем 25 марта.

Это упругое, подтянутое тело с гибкостью в безопасной анатомической амплитуде. Стабильность и свобода движений, дыхания, походки, лучше результаты в спорте и быту.

The military sleeping method claims to make you fall asleep in 2 minutes!
But does it actually work?
Step 1: Get into a comfortable position.
2: Flex your muscles, and then relax them,
starting from your head,
all the way down to your feet.
Step 3: Take deep breaths,
and either visualise yourself in a peaceful setting like a beach, lake,
or as a subscriber of this channel.
But repeating the words “don’t think, don’t think”
is the last thing I remember before falling asleep.
